DEPARTMENT OF HEALTH
97/087 Tuesday 6th May 1997

MONTHLY CREUTZFELDT-JAKOB FIGURES

The Department of Health is today issuing the latest monthly table,
giving the numbers of deaths of definite and probable cases of
Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease in the UK.

Year Referrals Deaths of definite and probable cases in the UK

Sporadi Iatroge Familia GSS nvCJD Total

1985 - 26 1 1 0 - 28
1986 - 26 0 0 0 - 26
1987 - 23 0 0 1 - 24
1988 - 21 1 1 0 - 23
1989 - 28 2 2 0 - 32
1990 53 27 5 0 0 - 32
1991 75 32 1 3 0 - 36
1992 96 44 2 4 1 - 51
1993 78 38 4 2 2 - 46
1994 116 53 1 2 3 - 59
1995 86 34 4 2 3 3 46
1996 129 38 4 2 3 10 57
31 5 0 0 0 1 6
1997*
============= previous month's data
1996 128 34 3 2 3 10 52
21 3 0 0 0 0 3
1997*

* To end February 1997. Total number of definite and probable
cases of nvCJD = 16 (including cases still alive and deaths since 28
February 1997).
====================

* To end March 1997. Plus two cases of definite nvCJD still alive.
Total number of definite and probable cases of nvCJD = 16

NOTES FOR EDITORS

1. The next table will be published on 2 June 1997.

Referrals: This is a simple count of all the cases which have been
referred to the Unit for further investigation in the year in
question. CJD may be no more than suspected; about half the cases
referred in the past have turned out not to be CJD.
***
