http://www.merc.com/stories/cgi/story.cgi?id=2798909-b64

10:54 AM ET 05/06/97

Britain confirms 16 human "mad cow" cases

LONDON (Reuter) - [MHJ - This report adds little to the information provided
above which Reuters obtained from the same source and then claimed
copyright. However, they also noted:]

One case of the new variant has been reported in France.

CJD normally strikes about one in a million. There were 57
cases in Britain last year.

[That makes one per million by my math - Mod.JW]

